'''Tenso Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine''' (天祖若宮八幡宮) is a {{ill|Shinto shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto shrine|qq=}} located in Sekimachikita 3-chome, {{ill|Nerima Ward|ja|練馬区|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nerima Ward|qq=}}, {{ill|Tokyo Metropolis|ja|東京都|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tokyo Metropolis|qq=}}, Japan. The shrine is situated atop a hill in {{ill|Musashiseki Park|ja|武蔵関公園|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Musashiseki Park|qq=}}, maintained by Nerima Ward.

== Overview ==

In [[1974]] ({{ill|Shōwa|ja|昭和|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shōwa|qq=}} 49), Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine and Tenso Shrine were merged and began to be collectively referred to as Tenso Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine.{{sfn|Nerima Ward Board of Education}}{{sfn|Tokyo Shrine Agency}} The enshrined deities include {{ill|Ōhirume-no-Muchi-no-Mikoto|ja|大日孁貴女尊|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ōhirume-no-Muchi-no-Mikoto|qq=}}, {{ill|Sayori Hime no Mikoto|ja|狭依姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sayori Hime no Mikoto|qq=}}, and {{ill|Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|ja|倉稲魂命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|qq=}} at Tenso Shrine. Wakamiya Hachiman Shrine venerates {{ill|Hachiman Ōkami|ja|八幡大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hachiman Ōkami|qq=}}, identified with {{ill|Emperor Ōjin|ja|応神天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Ōjin|qq=}}, and {{ill|Emperor Nintoku|ja|仁徳天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Nintoku|qq=}}. The main festival is held annually on September 28.{{sfn|Tokyo Shrine Agency}}

